ANDREW NEDZA, PROSECUTOR, v. NEW JERSEY DEPARTMENT OF LABOR ET AL., RESPONDENTS. Submitted May term, 1926 Decided October 7, 1926.

Before Justices Parker, Black and Campbell.

For the prosecutor, McCarter & English. For the respondents, Grosso, Brundage & Anderson. Per Curiam.

This was an application for a certiorari to review an order dismissing an application to. re-open an award by the deputy commissioner of the workmen’s compensation bureau dated December 18th, 1925.

The writ was refused by Mr. Justice Kalisch, and rightfully, as we think. The writ is therefore refused.
